        </media>
<caption>British chemist George Fownes, FRS (1815 – 1849).</caption>
      </figure>
   




    <para id="id1165172273578">In 1909 Fritz Haber (<link target-id="id1165184583059"/>) presented a method of ammonia synthesis to BASF. His work in collaboration with Carl Bosch (<link target-id="id1165189011828"/>) resulted in the process known as the Haber-Bosch process in which nitrogen and hydrogen are mixed at high temperature (600 °C) under pressure (200 atm) over an osmium catalyst, <link target-id="eip-244"/>. </para>

<equation id="eip-244">  <media id="id1165180741294_media" alt="">
          <image mime-type="image/jpg" src="../../media/graphics4-1aad.jpg" id="id1165180741294__onlineimage" width="500" print-width="4.5in"/>
        </media></equation>



