    <para id="id1165189973158">Addition of soda (sodium hydroxide, NaOH) to nitric acid results in the formation of sodium nitrate, <link target-id="eip-248"/>, which was the same fertilizer produced from the deposits in Chile. </para>

<equation id="eip-248">   <media id="id1165191104245_media" alt="">
          <image mime-type="image/jpg" src="../../media/graphics12-04fb.jpg" id="id1165191104245__onlineimage" width="500" print-width="4.5in"/>
        </media></equation>

     


